HEADWORD: Petaurist
<hw>Pe*tau"rist</hw> <pr>(p⟦esl⟧*t⟦add⟧"r⟦icr⟧st)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>petaurista</ets> a ropedancer, Gr.
<grk>petayristh`s</grk>, fr. <grk>petayri`zein</grk> to dance on a rope,
fr. <grk>pe`tayron</grk> a pole, a stage for ropedancers: cf. F.
<ets>p⟦eacute⟧tauriste</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any flying
marsupial of the genera <gen>Petaurus</gen>, <gen>Phalangista</gen>,
<gen>Acrobata</gen>, and allied genera. See <cref>Flying mouse</cref>,
under <er>Flying</er>, and <er>Phalangister</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

